Reference URL - https://aws.amazon.com/getting-started/hands-on/build-react-app-amplify-graphql/

AWS Amplify: (https://aws.amazon.com/amplify/?nc=sn&loc=0)

1. AWS Amplify is a complete solution that lets frontend web and mobile developers easily build, ship, and host full-stack applications on AWS, with the flexibility to leverage the breadth of AWS services as use cases evolve. No cloud expertise needed.
2. Create a cross-platform backend for your iOS, Android, Flutter, web, or React Native app with real-time and offline functionality in just a few clicks.
3. Visually build a pixel-perfect UI and connect your frontend UI to a cloud backend in clicks. AWS Amplify saves you from writing thousands of lines of code.
4. Easily deploy your web app or website to the fast, secure, and reliable AWS content delivery network (CDN), with hundreds of points of presence globally.

Project Accomplishment:

1. Hosting: Build and host a React application on the AWS global content delivery network (CDN)
2. Authentication: Add auth to your app to activate sign-in and sign-out
3. Database and storage: Add a GraphQL API, database, and storage solution
